Pour into a tumbler without straining and top up with more crushed ice if necessary. Garnish with mint. Enjoy.As some might know we are not always the best at jumping on the hypetrain but we only regret it sometimes. In this case we do. When @swetlanaholz  bar manager at Hamburg's @barlelion  went viral in the summer of 2021 with her La Boum cocktail - a kind of watermelon caipirinha - we really wanted to remix the drink. But we were so sluggish that various underage flatmates consistently munched away any melon we acquired before we could sacrifice it to the juicer.Now in 2022 we finally caught up with La Boum when it fought its way back into social media attention and onto various German bar menus along with the first rays of sunshine. And yes we missed out on a real awesome drink last year - fruity fresh light quaffable with a pretty new taste thanks to watermelon which is played far too seldom. 5 cl CachaÃ§a
3 cl Fresh lime juice
2 cl Sugar syrup
5 cl Fresh watermelon juice
1 Dash of Pimento Bitters

Put all ingredients together in a shaker and shake vigorously with crushed ice. Pour into a tumbler without straining and top up with more crushed ice if necessary. Garnish with mint. Enjoy.

As some might know  we are not always the best at jumping on the hypetrain  but we only regret it sometimes. In this case  we do. When @swetlanaholz   bar manager at Hamburg's @barlelion   went viral in the summer of 2021 with her La Boum cocktail - a kind of watermelon caipirinha - we really wanted to remix the drink. But we were so sluggish that various underage flatmates consistently munched away any melon we acquired  before we could sacrifice it to the juicer.

Now  in 2022  we finally caught up with La Boum when it fought its way back into social media attention and onto various German bar menus along with the first rays of sunshine. And yes  we missed out on a real awesome drink last year - fruity  fresh  light  quaffable  with a pretty new taste thanks to watermelon  which is played far too seldom. And itâ€™s such a nice drink to look at  also. Yeah  we should have listened to practically everyone else last year. Sorry.

main_text: The Mango called the â€œking of fruitsâ€ is the most widely consumed fruit in the world. Native to India and Southeast Asia where it has been cultivated for over 5000 years mango delivers on all levels. In addition to the juicy tropical flavour mango is an excellent source of vitamin C Vitamin A vitamin B6 folates and fibre. Mango not only contributes valuable nutrients it classified as a low glycaemic food which can be helpful for managing blood sugar levels.On the other hand; Watermelon as the name suggests is around 90% water which makes it useful for staying hydrated in the summer. Watermelon is native to Africa and has been cultivated since ancient times. It is a good source of vitamin C and contains decent amounts of potassium copper vitamin B5 and vitamin A. Sipping on watermelon juice after sweating is known to be beneficial too. {"1": {"comment_id": "missionaahar"  "comment_text": "BE YOUR OWN REASON TO SMILE.ğŸ˜„
The mandatory summer post. ğŸŒ
ğŸ‰Red colour of this amazing summer fruit comes from lycopene  an antioxidant which protects from sun burn. Lycopene may help protect against heart disease by reducing inflammation linked with HDL or good cholesterol.
ğŸ‰Watermelon is around 90% water and also provides electrolytes  such as potassium. This makes it a healthful choice of snack during the hot summer months.
ğŸ‰The fiber and water content in watermelon may aid your digestive health by supporting regular bowel movements.

ğŸ‰CAN DIABETIC EAT WATERMELON ?
Watermelon is a fruit with natural sugar content. People with diabetes must account for these carbs in their daily meal plan. It is better to consume watermelon whole rather than as a juice  as juicing removes the fiber  making the sugar easier for the body to absorb. This may increase the risk of a glucose spike.
ğŸ‰ Remember to watch portion sizes as with all fruit and juices.
